Reign: Reign of High Priest Painedjem II
Geography: Country of Origin Egypt, Upper Egypt; Thebes, Deir el-Bahri, Royal Cache, Tomb of Inhapi (TT 320), Burial of Nesikhonsu, Maspero 1881
Provenance: Excavated by Maspero, 1881. Acquired by of Rev. William MacGregor. MacGregor Collection sold at Sotheby, Wilkinson & Hodge, London, June 26-July 6, 1922 [lot 252]
purchased by Lord Carnarvon. Carnarvon Collection purchased by the Museum from Lady Carnarvon, 1926.
